rComments: Content was tough, but she really cared about making sure you understood it all. Final exam had no surprises in it as long as you came to class.
Just go to class and do the assignments and you will be fine. A little tough to follow the lecture at times, but was very easy to talk to when I approached her about things I did not understand.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Caring']

rComments: The midterm was decent and in-class examples seemed easy until the exam. Exam was extremely unfair and difficult, even with a cheat sheet. Practice questions and in class examples did not help AT ALL (they were much, much easier than what she actually tests on). Sometimes rude (passive aggressive, snarky comments)

Maria is very organized. Her lecture slides are really clear and are explained well in lecture. The assignments were pretty easy, save for some confusing points. She also gave 2% bonus if you filled out feedback sheets. Just do the homework and ask questions.

She seems like a nice person but her course is based solely on memorization. Grading is ridiculously unfair as you have to remember details of every single reading and lecture, but big picture concepts and application (AKA what every other uni course cares about) don't matter. She also gave a final essay, exam, and presentation all in 1 week.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Lots of homework', 'Tough grader']

rComments: Not caring at all, and sometimes went rude. Never listens to her students sincerely and, really, really, really, seldom shows respect to students. Tons of work to go, examples in the class were absolutely useless for exam/test preparation. Just can't think of more scientific comments to give.

I would never recommend her to anyone. Her exam was brutal and it was only her first semester teaching. She is not approachable and comes off as very rude. Examples done in class was nothing compared to what she tested us on.
